liquidateLiquidityPositions(Account.User.notice: liquidates all range positions in case the account is under watercharges a liquidation fee to the account and pays partially to the insurance fund and rest to the keeper.

liquidateTokenPosition(Account.UserInfo.notice: liquidates all range positions in case the account is under water

liquidityChange(Account.UserInfo storage.notice: changes range liquidity 'vToken' of market value equal to 'vTokenNotional'if 'liquidityDelta'>0 then liquidity is added and if 'liquidityChange'<0 then liquidity is removedthe liquidity change is reverted if the sqrt price at the time of execution is beyond 'slippageToleranceBps' of 'sqrtPriceCurrent' suppliedwhenever liquidity change is done the internal token position is taken out. If 'closeTokenPosition' is true this is swapped out else it is added to the current token position

removeLimitOrder(Account.UserInfo storag.notice: removes limit order based on the current price position (keeper call)

removeProfit(Account.UserInfo storage,ui.notice: removes 'amount' of profit generated in base token

swapToken(Account.UserInfo storage,IVTok.notice: swaps 'vToken' of token amount equal to 'swapParams.amount'if vTokenAmount>0 then the swap is a long or close short and if vTokenAmount<0 then swap is a short or close longisNotional specifies whether the amount represents token amount (false) or base amount(true)isPartialAllowed specifies whether to revert (false) or to execute a partial swap (true)sqrtPriceLimit threshold sqrt price which if crossed then revert or execute partial swap
